.TH GIT\-ISSUE\-SEARCH 1 "2026-02-07" "git-issue 1.0.0" "Git Issue Manual"
.SH NAME
git\-issue\-search \- search issues by text pattern
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git issue search
.I <pattern>
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Search issue titles, bodies, and comments for a text pattern.
The pattern is matched as a fixed string by default (not a regular
expression).
.PP
Matching issues are listed with their ID, state, and title.
Up to 5 matching lines per issue are shown with line numbers.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-state " " \fI<state>\fR
Filter by state:
.BR open ", " closed ", " all " (default)."
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-ignore\-case
Case-insensitive search.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show usage information.
.SH EXAMPLES
Search for a string:
.RS
.nf
$ git issue search "timeout"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Case-insensitive search in open issues only:
.RS
.nf
$ git issue search "login" -i -s open
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git\-issue (1),
.BR git\-issue\-ls (1)
